==>Handling checkboxes and radiobuttons:
    *If only 1 checkbox or 1 radiobutton, you can just click on it
    *If you have multiple choices, you can store them in a List and loop through (just like multiple WebElements)

==>DropDowns
    *a menu which gives us an opportunity to select one or more options
    *2 Types:
        1)Single Select
        2)Multiple Select
    *Handling DropDowns:
        1)Click on DropDowns and click on Option
        2)Using Select Class //tag of dropdown must have select tagname if this option is used
    *Selection an Option from a DropDown can be done in 3 ways:
        1)by index
        2)by visible text
        3)by value
    *Whenever multiple elements are interacted with, you store them inside the container such as List, Set, etc and select.getOptions
    *In order to deselect the option from dropdown
        -->Make sure dropdown is multiple select
        -->deselectByValue()
        -->deselectByVisible()
        -->deselectByIndex()
        -->deselectAll()